Character class

Variables
String chosenClass
String chosenName
String location

Constructor
public Character(String class, String name)
- get user to input "warrior" or "mage" based on what class they want
- set their chosen class to a variable to be used in methods
- set their chosen name to a variable to be used in methods

public Character()
- randomizes a character by randomly picking between one of the two classes, and randomly picks from 1 of 10 names
- sets the class and name to variables

Methods

inventory method
- creates an inventory for the user to store items
- items to heal/do specific actions
- displays the inventory when the command is run

healthbar method
- creates a healthbar for the user
- goes down everytime the user is attacked
- once it reaches 0, user loses
- user has different options in order to get their health back up
- use items, rest
- warrior has more health than mage

random location method
- randomizes the location that the user starts at and sets it to a variable
- three different locations
- forest, cave, desert
- different enemies based on the location

abilities method
- changes abilities based on the class user picks
- four different abilities for both classes
- two options for attack, two for defense
- warrior attacks: one hit, high dmg/ multi-hit(random chance for hits), low dmg
- warrior defense: block(lessens dmg taken)/roll(chance to avoid all dmg)
- mage attacks: one hit, high dmg, chance for burn dmg(fireball)/one hit, high dmg, chance the enemy is paralyzed(thunderbolt)
- mage defense: block(blocks all dmg)/heal(heals some of the healthbar)

battle method
- choose between attack and defense
- has two options for attack and defense based on user's class
- enemy's choice is randomized
- higher chance for enemy to attack when user healthbar is low

randomized enemies method
- randomizes the enemies that the user meets
- sets the enemies that can be chosen based on the location
- four different enemies each location
- user has to defeat at least two different enemies to progress
- boss?

movement method
- allows for the user to move through the location
- user can move north, south, east, west
- different directions have different endings depending on what paths you go on
- different paths can intersect

win location method
- sets a place that the user has to get to in order to win
- once the user has moved through the correct locations and has beaten the required enemies, they win

Adventure class
- Welcomes the user to the location that they start in
- Asks for their name and class, or the user can press a key to randomize the selection
- Displays the user's character and abilities
- Begins the adventure by asking what they want to do
- Use a while loop for the movement and randomized enemies
- Use while loop for battle
- If the character dies, the user loses
- Once the user's character gets to a specific location, they win
- Display their total stats